5.12.23  6:04 pm   Ok so like, I was wondering what the point of life was, and I figured out that it was the dot on the i of life, which is in fact a point, but then I wanted to find the meaning of life, so I thought that the meaning of life must mean the mean of life, so I translated all the letters of life alphanumerically until L=12, I=9, F=6, E=5, then I found the mean of that dataset which is 8, and then I realized that if you combined the mean of life and the point of life, you would truly have the answer to life so that makes .8 and now the word life is missing its point which makes it llfe, but at least now we have the true answer to life, but then I remembered that the answer to life the universe and everything was 42, so I reasoned that to find the answer to just the universe and everything, you must subtract the answer to life from the answer to life the universe and everything, meaning that the answer to the universe and everything is 41.2, but then I wondered which part of that is the universe and which part of that is everything, and I realized that since everything contains the universe as well as infinite nothingness, and since the universe is not inf inite, then the value of the universe actually approaches 0, and thus every thing must be made out of 41.2 nothingnesses. If you've made it this far you might be wondering why life has a value when it to is not infinite, and the answer is that life contains some of the infinite nothingness, for example my life is full of infinite nothingness, which is why I'm happy to say that life definitely equals .8
